This article is about an executive order issued by President Barack Obama regarding the order of succession within the Department of Veterans Affairs. The order establishes that, in the event that both the Secretary and the Deputy Secretary of Veterans Affairs are unable to perform their duties, certain officials within the department will act as Secretary in a specific order. The order also states that individuals serving in an acting capacity in any of these positions cannot act as Secretary under this order, and the President has the discretion to depart from this order when designating an acting Secretary. The executive order also revokes previous orders and memorandums related to the designation of officers within the Department of Veterans Affairs. Finally, it states that the order does not create any legal rights or benefits against the United States or any other party.